# S10: Safe Area, Layout Orientation & Dev Polish

## Objective
Fix the layout gaps visible in device testing (portrait safe-area band, landscape column
stacking) and developer friction (Tone.js console noise, auto game-over during layout work).
Portrait behaviour stays as-is; landscape switches to horizontal row layouts where specified.

## Context (from user screenshots + audit)
- Status bar shows white band above content — MuseCool lacks NaviTrack-style safe-area plumbing.
- Game + Start screens stack note/mascot vertically in landscape; user wants them side-by-side, vertically centered on each other.
- StartScreen calls `preload()` on mount → Sampler/AudioContext before user gesture.
- GameScreen auto-navigates to GameOver on `phase === 'gameover'` — blocks layout iteration.
- Favicon is generic purple asset; mascot (Melody) should be the brand mark.

## Track A — Foundation (must complete before layout)
- [x] S10-T01-SafeAreaFoundation.pd
- [x] S10-T02-ToneLazyInit.pd
- [x] S10-T03-LayoutTestFlag.pd
