## Track B — Orientation layouts (after Track A)
- [x] S10-T05-GameScreenOrientationLayout.pd
- [x] S10-T06-StartScreenOrientationLayout.pd
- [x] S10-T07-GameOverSpacingPass.pd
- [x] S10-T08-OrientationLayoutQA.pd

## Landscape layout contract

| Screen | Portrait | Landscape |
|---|---|---|
| Game (Find) | Column: ring → mascot → piano | Row: ring + mascot centred on each other; piano full width below |
| Start | Column: title → tagline → mascot → Play → piano | Row: copy + CTA left, mascot right; hide assistive piano |
| GameOver | Column panel centred | Compact panel; tighter padding; CTA always visible |

## Safe-area contract (ported from NaviTrack)
- `viewport-fit=cover` + `black-translucent` (already in index.html — verify).
- Body/html extend gradient into notch; `padding-top: env(safe-area-inset-top)`.
- Piano/footer: `padding-bottom: max(env(safe-area-inset-bottom), 0px)`.
- Landscape: horizontal insets via `--pwa-spacing-x` / `--pwa-spacing-r` on screen roots.

## Definition of Done
- Zero white status-bar band on iOS simulator PWA; gradient fills safe areas.
- Console clean on cold load (no AudioContext/Tone warnings before first tap).
- `VITE_LAYOUT_TEST=true` keeps game screen after game-over for layout QA.
- Favicon + PWA icons show mascot idle face (teal/orange brand).
- All three screens pass 375×667 portrait and 667×375 landscape without scroll/clipped CTAs.
